John,<br>
     Your last two posts are some of the best examples I have ever seen of the art of someone trying their absolute best to royally piss off anybody who might just agree with one's original point.  Flash! - If you've checked any of the other threads; you would surely noticed that you're not the only one carrying a good deal of pain from the war.  I'm sorry you're still hurting inside badly, but that doesn't give you the right to automatically assume the worst of anyone in political power when you went to Vietnam or in power now.  Assuming the worst motives makes you no better than Limbaugh's ditto heads.<br>
     If you had done your homework; you would have found that the flag desecration amendment originated with WWII era veterans, especially those in the American Legion.  Congress is just paying attention to those constituents that are screaming the loudest right now.  That's one reason why the amendment process was made a bit difficult; so that a constitutional change would not be made in the emotional heat of the moment.<br>
    I don't believe in deifying the flag, but I refuse to call it a &quot;rag&quot; either.  There is no nation on this earth with completely clean hands in its history, but that does not mean a nation's flag ceases to stand for the best of what that nation is.  If you can't accept that; you had better look for Utopia (&quot;No Place&quot; as defined by Thomas More) on some other planet; because no nation on this one will ever be perfect enough for you. 
